(name 'GitFileTree-MergeDriver-ThierryGoubier.8' message 'Use STON for json data' id 'fb88265d-6224-0d00-a573-8ff20ff5b967' date '22 March 2018' time '2:53:05.440478 pm' author 'ThierryGoubier' ancestors ((name 'GitFileTree-MergeDriver-HolgerHansPeterFreyther.7' message 'Allow merge to be used with git mergetool

E.g. when using git rebase the normal git-merge tool does not seem to be
used. Re-use the existing mergers and deal with the different formats. I am
not fully sure it works all right but on first merge it seemed to have done the
right thing (even if version didn''t change).

~/.gitconfig:
[mergetool "mcmerge"]
        cmd = /GitFileTree-MergeDriver/merge --mergetool $BASE $LOCAL $REMOTE $MERGED

git mergetool --tool=mcmerge
